[LEO]
Uh, Patrick,

66
00:04:21,291 --> 00:04:22,666
I think you've had one too many!

67
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,041
Enough, Patrick.

68
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,583
How've you been, Leo?

69
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,666
Do you feel like you're
getting settled into the city?

70
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:30,875
[LEO]
More or less.

71
00:04:32,791 --> 00:04:34,208
I mean,

72
00:04:34,291 --> 00:04:36,875
I am still getting used to
some of the abrupt weirdness.

73
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:38,291
Like today on the subway.

74
00:04:38,375 --> 00:04:40,291
I saw this person who
had the most incredible

75
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:41,750
crimson aura around them,

76
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:43,375
and I thought "That's awesome".

77
00:04:43,458 --> 00:04:45,291
And I sort of said it out loud

78
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:47,208
because I was so surprised.

79
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:48,166
Huh?

80
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,000
Leonardo,

81
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,541
this aura,

82
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,958
would you say that it looked
like red wings made of light?

83
00:04:57,041 --> 00:04:58,541
Stretching out from them?

84
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:01,291
[LEO]
Uh, yeah, that's right.

85
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:03,750
[STARPHASE]
All right, to be specific,

86
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,958
was it this color?

87
00:05:05,041 --> 00:05:06,458
[LEO]
Yeah. Exactly.

88
00:05:06,541 --> 00:05:07,791
[MAN 1]
Seriously?

89
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:09,333
[MAN 2]
Dammit

90
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:10,666
[LEO]
Is that a problem?

91
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:11,791
What gives?

92
00:05:12,958 --> 00:05:14,583
Oh, poor naive Leo.

93
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,708
Let me enlighten you, my son.

94
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:20,291
Seriously? You gonna pull
the condescending mentor act?

95
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:21,916
Is that really helpful?

96
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,291
What you saw, my dumb pupil,

97
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:24,500
was a vampire.

98
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,208
[LEO]
Okay, so what did I really see?

99
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:34,166
Did I not just tell you?

100
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,083
[STARPHASE]
"Noble beings shrouded

101
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:39,083
with shimmering, scarlet wings".

102
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:42,208
That's how they're described
in ancient documents.

103
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:43,875
After lifetimes of research,

104
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:46,250
it's been proven that
they do actually exist,

105
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:49,125
but they remain an
elusive phenomenon,

106
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:50,500
incapable of being detected

107
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:53,000
by any optical
instruments or sensors.

108
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:54,250
[LEO]
I'm still having trouble

109
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:55,541
swallowing this one.

110
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:56,958
[ZAPP]
Then I'll beat it

111
00:05:57,041 --> 00:06:00,083
down your skeptical throat,
you freakin' smart ass!

112
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:01,125
[KK]
I'm willing to bet

113
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:02,666
it was an elder
that the kid saw,

114
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:04,500
which would be
a million times worse

115
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,666
than the trash
we normally encounter.

116
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,000
[KLAUS]
With Leo's eyes,

117
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,500
we can actually
obtain information

118
00:06:09,583 --> 00:06:11,708
that we've all only
previously dreamt of.

119
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:14,083
I think it's time
to call in the specialist.

120
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:16,958
[AUDIENCE complains]

121
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:18,416
[KK]
Is it really necessary

122
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,875
to call him in?

123
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:21,541
Realistically,

124
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:23,750
he'll probably show up
even if we don't ask him to.

125
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:27,458
Can you picture him
not showing up

126
00:06:27,541 --> 00:06:29,208
for a situation like this?

127
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,750
So who is this guy?

128
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,291
Uh, Zapp?

129
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:48,875
Achoo!

130
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:51,708
[LEO]
"Lucky Abrams", huh?

131
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:53,583
[ZAPP]
Yeah, and to put it lightly,

132
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:55,541
he's one of the world's
most revered authorities

133
00:06:55,625 --> 00:06:57,208
on vampire activity.

134
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,833
The chief considers
him to be his mentor.

135
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:02,125
[LEO]
His mentor?

136
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:04,666
The chief was in the
game long before this.

137
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,666
Then again, that
goes for all of us.

138
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,916
We used to be underground
monster hunters.

139
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,708
The chief put down plenty
of them in his solo days.

140
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:13,666
You knew all of that, right?

141
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,666
Sure.

142
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,916
[ZAPP]
Just to give you a heads up,

143
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,583
nobody gets a
nickname like "Lucky"

144
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:20,458
because they have good luck.

145
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:22,083
[LEO]
Then why's he called that?

146
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:23,916
[ABRAMS]
Zapp!

147
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:26,333
--There you are!
--[BOTH] Huh?

148
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:38,875
Zapp!

149
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,000
Jeez, look at this mess.

150
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:42,583
This city is even more dangerous

151
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:43,958
than I remember.

152
00:07:45,916 --> 00:07:52,375
You'd need nine
lives to live here.

153
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:54,416
[ZAPP]
Uh, Mr. Abrams?

154
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,500
Not to be rude here,

155
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:59,625
but could you keep a distance
of about 10 feet from me?

156
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:02,208
[ABRAMS]
Hey!

157
00:08:02,291 --> 00:08:03,583
Look at this lot!

158
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:05,458
How're you no-goodniks doing?

159
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:07,250
Klaus, my boy!

160
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,958
Same big old lug
you always were.

161
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,041
You still workin' as
hard as the world works

162
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,791
to keep you from doing any work?

163
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:16,333
We had a strong suspicion

164
00:08:16,416 --> 00:08:17,791
that you might be
arriving shortly.

165
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,666
Really, I'm surprised
to hear that.

166
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:23,041
I didn't tell anyone
beforehand I was coming.

167
00:08:23,125 --> 00:08:24,375
[GILBERT]
A plane unexpectedly exploded

168
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:25,916
at the airport earlier.

169
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,208
I doubt you need me to spell
out what exactly this portends.

170
00:08:29,291 --> 00:08:30,375
[STARPHASE]
He's here.

171
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:31,541
[CHAIN]
Here he comes.

172
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:33,666
[GILBERT]
I should up my life insurance.

173
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:36,208
[ABRAMS laughs]

174
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,375
[ABRAMS]
You took that as

175
00:08:37,458 --> 00:08:39,208
a signal of my imminent arrival?

176
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,083
Guess you got me there.

177
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,125
[ABRAMS]
I nearly got flattened

178
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:48,375
by a truck on my way over here,
but fate spared me!

179
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:50,291
[ZAPP]
Have you figured it out yet?

180
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,000
Where he got his nickname from

181
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:53,541
and why we're all
terrified of him?

182
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:57,875
[indistinct speaking,
animal noises]

183
00:09:02,666 --> 00:09:04,000
[SHEEP baaing]

184
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:10,250
[ROOSTER crowing]

185
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,083
So you're Leonardo?

186
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:13,708
[LEO]
Uh, yes?

187
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:17,041
Is it true? You're the holder of
the All-seeing Eyes of the Gods?

188
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:18,291
Yes.

189
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,041
Why didn't you say so sooner?

190
00:09:23,916 --> 00:09:25,000
[ABRAMS]
I need you

191
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:26,208
to lay your eyes on this for me.

192
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,375
[LEO]
Um, the hand?

193
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,541
[ABRAMS]
That is no ordinary hand.

194
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:35,916
You see?

195
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,541
This hand's our only direct
link to the Elder 13.

196
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:40,875
There is only one
known recorded incident

197
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,541
throughout history in
which our society.

198
00:09:42,625 --> 00:09:45,333
has come face to
face with an elder.

199
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:47,958
The ghastly beast singlehandedly

200
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:50,083
took over an entire battleship,

201
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:52,500
and then, as if to mock us,

202
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:55,291
it erected a giant cross
made from the flesh

203
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:59,250
and severed limbs of
the 343 crew members on board.

204
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,375
Furthermore,

205
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:03,916
we've lost the lives
of 47 of our agents

206
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,333
who were tasked with
protecting this hand.

207
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:07,916
To be more precise,

208
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
they lost their lives
while trying to obtain

209
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:12,750
the scrap of paper
the hand is clutching.

210
00:10:15,458 --> 00:10:18,916
Even separated from its body,
it tenaciously clings.

211
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,541
We presume there to
be a list written upon it.

212
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:23,500
A list composed of
the true names

213
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:26,333
of the Elder 13 Blood Breed.

214
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,833
There is power to
be found in a name

215
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,958
and they fervently
protect this power

216
00:10:31,041 --> 00:10:33,791
beneath a cast iron
cloak of anonymity.

217
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:38,208
Now, try to read this.

218
00:10:38,291 --> 00:10:39,916
With all your might,

219
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,625
expose their uttermost
guarded vulnerability.

220
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:45,208
Reveal their true identities!

221
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:57,458
[ZAPP]
Leo!

222
00:10:57,541 --> 00:10:58,875
[KLAUS]
Are you all right?

223
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:03,250
Well that was friggin' freaky.

224
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:07,458
Huh? What the--

225
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:11,500
Um, Klaus,

226
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:12,791
the light--

227
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:14,041
It keeps

228
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:15,000
getting more--

229
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,208
[KLAUS]
Leonardo!

230
00:11:18,791 --> 00:11:20,166
[train horn]

231
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,625
[ZAPP]
You see that?

232
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:37,458
That giant mystical whatever

233
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,666
just got taken out
by a meteorite!

234
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:42,750
I've seen some weird crap
but never anything like that!

235
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:45,333
We are not the only ones
aboard this subway, Zapp.

236
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:46,916
Please lower your voice.

237
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,666
I sincerely doubt something like
that is so unusual around here.

238
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,125
It's freakishly unusual!

239
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:53,541
[screaming]

240
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:55,500
Why the hell wasn't somebody

241
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:58,625
besides me available
to come here with you?

242
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:02,250
[ZAPP]
The chief just looks like

243
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:05,208
he's happy to take the
train for a change.

244
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:07,666
And aside from his
intelligence and luck,

245
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:09,833
he's just like any
other normal guy.

246
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,791
Is he gonna be okay?

247
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:16,083
His eyes are in
an amplified state.

248
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:18,250
They've become
intractably perceptive,

249
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:20,666
and his vision seems
to be peering into

250
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:22,666
the furthest depths of reality.

251
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,916
This just might be our chance.

252
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,416
[bells tolling]

253
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,416
We'll finally see the Elders
lurking on the other side.

254
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,125
